wikipedia_page.main: Eliza Walker Dunbar (4 November 1845 – 25 August 1925) was a Scottish physician and the first woman from the UK to qualify and work as a doctor.

Wait was converted to the cause of women's suffrage by the forced resignation of Eliza Walker Dunbar from the Bristol Royal Hospital for Children. His daughter Frances Katharine Wait married Charles Chadwyck-Healey on 17 May 1884.
